include ../../partials/mixins

doctype html
html
  head
    +head("Chemistry Calculators")
    link(rel="shortcut icon" href="../../assets/icons/chemistry.png")
    link(rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="../../uikit.css")
    link(rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href=require("katex/dist/katex.css").default)
    link(rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="../../global.css")
    link(rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css")
  body
    +container(["projects", "chemistry"])
      div(uk-grid)
        div(class="uk-width-medium@m")
          ul.uk-tab-left.uk-tab-stacked(uk-tab uk-sticky="offset: 40; media: @m" uk-switcher="connect: #switcher; animation: uk-animation-fade")
            li: a(href="#") Molar Mass
            li.uk-disabled: a(href="#") Dilution
            li.uk-disabled: a(href="#") Ideal Gas Law
            li.uk-disabled: a(href="#") Specific Heat Capacity
        .uk-width-expand.uk-margin-remove-top
          #switcher.uk-switcher
            div
              h3 Molar Mass Calculator
              p In chemistry, the #[a.uk-link(href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Molar_mass") molar mass] is a physical property that is defined as the mass of a substance divided by the amount of the substance. This calculator solves for the molar mass of a chemical formula and the mass percent of each element in the formula.
              p
                | Example:
                | The chemical formula for magnesium stearate, a compound found in some medical tablets, is #[span(data-katex-expr="\\displaystyle Mg \\left(CH_3 \\left(CH_2 \\right)_{16}CO_2 \\right)_2")] and would be entered below as Mg(CH3(CH2)16CO2)2.
              #molarMassInput.uk-inline.uk-width-1-1
                a.uk-form-icon.uk-form-icon-flip(uk-icon="close")
                input.uk-input(type="text" placeholder="Chemical formula")
              #molarMassFormulaContainer.uk-margin-small
                #molarMassFormula.uk-text-center
                #molarMassInputError.uk-text-danger(hidden)
              table#molarMassTable.uk-table.uk-table-small.uk-table-divider
                thead
                  th Element
                  th Atoms
                  th Mass In Compound (g / mol)
                  th Mass Percent
                tbody
                tfoot
                  tr
                    td Total:
                    td 0
                    td 0.0000
                    td
            div Under construction
            div Under construction
            div Under construction
